When the world ends and the silver trumpets sound....ozzy will be there in the sky drawn from the clouds singing us to the ever after what ever it may be.

We don't have long left with him relative to how long we've had him. I am blessed as are we all, for being able to have lived with these amazing artists who orchestrated our thoughts, imaginations and our lives. snippet.textDisplay: You Ozzy won't die an ordinary man .You are the Prince of Darkness. Lol August a couple years back in a little town called Center field I think it was I llinois. The Moon eclipse Ozzy n Zak Wylde played it was like a Wood stock so many ppl in a field it took no time to get there but leaving it took 5 hours the line of traffic was unbelievable. But it was the best concert I'd ever been to and I have been to a lot of concerts. Any who Nahko was playing in St. Louis for The moon eclispe also I heard there was a ceremony place built up. Cause the Natives believed that we had to make lots of noise, beat the drums loud so the frog wouldn't eat the moon .If the frog ate the moon during the eclipse it was the end of times . Great artist Nahko is and so I was planning on finding away to St. Louis for that but this dear friend instead invited me to go see Ozzy n Zak. Knowing I am a hugh super hugh fan of Ozzy n Sharron n the kids now grown lol. But what drew me to Rock n roll it was kinda bad at home growing up so I went in my room closed out the arguing with the radio. Here comes this guitar that gave me goose bumps .Randy Rhodes I was in love still am lol.after R.I.P Randy Rhodes past I was lost the guitar music was epic. Then I hear Ozzy with this new guy to me it was like Zak Wylde had Randy Rhodes in him lol. Ok anyways sorry got off track I went to Moon stock in Centerfield, Illinois to see Ozzy n Zak jam to Bark at the Moon during the Moon eclipse. Listening to the radio and the rumors it's the end of times Ozzy is playing the Prince of Darkness during the one n only moon eclipse . It was amazing 1:30 on in the afternoon hot as hell. Here comes Ozzy n Zak jamming Bark at the Moon all a sudden it got dark like night time and cold. Then it was back to daylight n hot sweaty August. Once in a life time amazing something I will never forget .I have awesome pictures of Ozzy n Zak the rest of the band God bless ya all .The awesome music guitars n drums at Moonstock and Nahko in St. Louis with the Native American Indians beating the drums so loud to distract the frog from eating the moon. We're all still here with great memories,good times and Ozzy you my man have accomplished many of those good times thru my years with Black Sabbath ,Ozzfest ,Moon stock, The Osbournes .I love you man and this song is awesome also .But you my friend are no ordinary man .You are amazing The Prince of Darkness. Thank you Ozzy for all the good times the good memories the good music the best in my world Randy Rhodes then Zak Wylde . Thank you for sharing your talent and showing us all love thru good n bad. You Rock n so does Sharron. Man I love her and no I'm not gay no offense taken to anybody please . Sweet Leaf, Fairies Wear Boots with Sabbath to Diary of a Madman my favorite with Randy Rhodes to No Rest for the Wicked Zak Wylde .Super Amazing .Ozzy thank you you saved me from child hood good times n bad times Ozzy was always there being a inspiration feeding our souls to making us laugh to shedding a tea.r .I love you guys .

snippet.textDisplay: Ozzy has one of the most perfect voices. He sounds as good raw, onstage as on the albums. He is one of my heroes. He's never been scared to let his pain and anger, his love and life play out for the world to see. He is brutally raw and I admire his fierce way of living. Bravo Oz! You are a legend in your own time. A wonderful display of talent and fierceness. Sharon is a badass and I love you both. I am a 48 yr old grandmother and my grandkids and kids can sing all of Ozzy's songs. Even the good ole Sabbath days. I am a fan from my childhood so it's been a long time of following Ozzy's music. I have seen him perform several times and I'm always thrilled, never have I been disappointed. Rock on Ozzy!
